# criar compartimento
    - acessar oracle cloud
        cloud acconunt
        username
        password
    
    - criação compartimento (para isolar as instancias)
        option (3 barras horizontais) -> Identity -> Compartments
        
        - Create Compartment
            Name (nome do compartimento)
            Description (descrição do compartimento)
            Parent Compartment (compartimento Pai - escolher compartimento)
            Tag Key (Tag para identificação das instancias/VNIC/BLOCK VOLUME/BUCKET, etc...)
    
    - criar instancia
        - option (3 barras horizontais) -> Compute -> Instances
        
        - Create Instance
            Name (nome da instancia)
            Create in compartment (definir qual compartimento sera criada a instancia)
            Placement and hardware -> edit
                Availability domain (definir disponibilidade)
                Image (escolha o Sistema Operacional)
                Shape (definir a configuração de hardware da instancia)
            
            - Networking -> edit
                - caso nao tenha criado VNC
                    - option (3 barras horizontais) -> Networking -> Virtual Cloud Networks
                        - Create VCN
                            name (nome da VCN)
                            CREATE IN COMPARTMENT (escolher compartimento)
                            CIDR Blocks (para teste "10.0.0.0/16")
                            DNS RESOLUTION
                                USE DNS HOSTNAMES IN THIS VCN (marcado)
                                                    
                            - SUBNET
                            - Create subnet
                                NAME (nome da subnet da VCN)
                                CREATE IN COMPARTMENT (escolher compartimento)
                                SUBNET TYPE (Recomendação da Oracle "regional")
                                CIDR BLOCK (para teste "10.0.0.0/24")
                                ROUTE TABLE COMPARTMENT IN <COMPARTMENT_NAME>
                                SUBNET ACCESS (Public Subnet)
                                DNS RESOLUTION
                                    USE DNS HOSTNAMES IN THIS SUBNET (marcado)
                                DHCP OPTIONS COMPARTMENT IN <COMPARTMENT_NAME>
                                    (default)
                                Security Lists
                                    (default)
                                Create subnet

                            - Internet Gateways
                            - Create Internet Gateway
                                NAME (nome do gateway)
                                CREATE IN COMPARTMENT (escolher compartimento)
                                Create Internet Gateway
                            
                            - Route Tables
                                (selecionar Route Table)
                                    Add Route Rules
                                        TARGET TYPE (Internet Gateway)
                                        DESTINATION CIDR BLOCK (para teste "0.0.0.0/0")
                                        TARGET INTERNET GATEWAY IN <COMPARTMENT_NAME> (escolher Internet gatway)
                                        Add Route Rules
                
                - caso ja tenha criado VCN
                    Network
                        Virtual cloud network in <COMPARTMENT_NAME>
                            (escolher VCN)
                    Subnet
                        Subnet in <COMPARTMENT_NAME>
                            (escolher subnet)
                    Public IP Address
                        Assign a public IPv4 address (marcar)

            - Add SSH keys
                Paste public keys (marcar)
                    - caso nao tenha chave SSH
                        - abrir puttygen
                            - Parameters
                                - Type of key to generate:
                                    RSA
                                - Numbers of bits in a generate key:
                                    2048
                            - Generate (clicar)
                            - key
                                "Public key for pasting into Openssh authorized_keys file:"
                                copiar TODO TEXTO
                                    colar na criação da instancia
                                    option (3 barras horizontais) -> Compute -> Instances -> Create Instance -> Add SSH keys -> SSH keys
                            - Save the generated key
                                Save public key (definir local seguro no HD)
                                save private key (definir local seguro no HD)
                    
                    - caso ja tenha chave SSH
                        colar chave SSH
                            option (3 barras horizontais) -> Compute -> Instances -> Create Instance -> Add SSH keys -> SSH keys
            
            - CREATE

# acessar OCI
    Oracle Cloud
        Compute -> Instances -> Instance Details
            Instance Information
                Instance Access -> Public IP Address (copiar)
    - abrir putty
        - category -> sessions
            Host name 
                ip da oracle cloud copiado
            Connection Type
                SSH
            Saved Sessions
                (nome da conexão <escolha>)
        - category -> SSH -> Auth
            Pivate key file for authentication
                (Browse...) -> localizar private key salva
        - category -> sessions -> load, save or delete a stored session
            Save
        - Open
            (1° conexão: clicar em "SIM")
            login as: opc
            mensagem esperada
                Authenticating with public key "<private_key>"
                Last login: <date> from <IP>
            
            login root
                sudo su -
            
            - localização do user "opc"
                Oracle Cloud
                    Compute -> Instances -> Instance Details
                        Instance Information
                            Instance Access -> Username
